{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idaba935dc-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s12685"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"12685"},"text":"§ 12685.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Reserves separated for cause: character of discharge","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"A member of a reserve component who is separated for cause, except under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s12684"},"text":"section 12684 of this title","children":[],"tail":", is entitled to a discharge under honorable conditions unless—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaba935dd-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s12685/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the member is discharged under conditions other than honorable under an approved sentence of a court-martial or under the approved findings of a board of officers convened by an authority designated by the Secretary concerned; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaba935de-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s12685/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the member consents to a discharge under conditions other than honorable with a waiver of proceedings of a court-martial or a board.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idaba935df-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/337/dA/tXVI/s1662/i/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–337, div. A, title XVI, § 1662(i)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-05"},"text":"Oct. 5, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/2998"